<subSubSection id="C348A2CCD649DC0222CEFD74B625672B" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEDF147D649DC0222CEFD74B625672B" blockId="14.[151,1436,231,578]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B9262D55D649DC0222CEFD74B33B6413" bold="true" box="[198,319,351,377]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species, described in 
<taxonomicName id="4C528AC4D649DC022086FD4BB17F6413" authority="" box="[654,891,352,377]" genus="Mylabris" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Gorrizia">
<emphasis id="B9262D55D649DC022086FD4BB17F6413" box="[654,891,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Mylabris (Gorrizia)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(a taxon presently referred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C528AC4D649DC0226FCFD4BB7566413" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" box="[1268,1362,352,377]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9262D55D649DC0226FCFD4BB7566413" box="[1268,1362,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Hycleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), was referred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C528AC4D649DC02239AFDA3B03D64CB" authorityName="Pardo Alcaide" authorityYear="1950" box="[402,569,392,417]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Croscherichia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9262D55D649DC02239AFDA3B03D64CB" box="[402,569,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Croscherichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC38CB6D649DC02206EFDA3B18364C8" author="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Pinto, J. D." box="[614,903,392,418]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="2013 - 2102" refId="ref23068" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Pinto, J. D. (2002) The Old World genera of Meloidae (Coleoptera): a key and synopsis. Journal of Natural History, 36, 2013 - 2102." type="journal article" year="2002">Bologna &amp; Pinto (2002)</bibRefCitation>
. Actually this placement needs confirmation, because the mesosternum and aedeagus are typical of this genus, as well as the elytral pattern, antennal and protibial setation of female. However, the species is strongly distinct by the male tibial and antennal features described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC38CB6D649DC022333FE2BB3E96770" author="Kaszab, Z." box="[315,493,512,538]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="144 - 204" refId="ref23584" refString="Kaszab, Z. (1983) Insects of Saudi Arabia. Coleoptera: Fam. Meloidae - A synopsis of the Arabian Meloidae. Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 5, 144 - 204." type="journal article" year="1983">Kaszab (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, by the external hind spur not greatly thickened but only spoon-like, and the female protarsi very short and robust, differently than in other 
<emphasis id="B9262D55D649DC02217BFE03B625672B" box="[883,1057,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="4C528AC4D649DC02217BFE03B619672B" authorityName="Pardo Alcaide" authorityYear="1950" box="[883,1053,552,577]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Croscherichia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Croscherichia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
